The Governors of the 36 states of the federations has agreed to ensure that the implementation of the financial autonomy for judiciary and state legislative assemblies will commence by the end of May this year.  The timeline for the autonomy implementation was disclosed by the Chairman Nigeria Governors Forum (NGF), Dr Kayode Fayemi in Abuja on Monday, after a meeting between the Chief of Staff to the President, the Solicitor General of the Federation, representatives of Speakers of State Houses of Assembly and some Governors after modalities for the implementation was agreed upon.Â Governor Fayemi of Ekiti state maintained that the 36 Governors have never been against the financial autonomy implementation but the modalities.  Our Correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that the NGF Chairman appealed to members of the Judicial Staff Union of Nigeria (JUSUN) to suspend the ongoing strike in the interest of the nation.  Meanwhile, the Nigerian Governors Forum (NGF) also said it was not necessary for it to react to the allegation by Governor Godwin Obaseki of Edo state that N60 billion was printed by the Federal Government in March, 2021 to augment monthly allocation to the 36 states and the Federal Capital Territory (FCT).